<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i> ssp. <i>spiciformis</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i> or <i>Symphoricarpos</i> <i>rotundifolius</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Amelanchier</i> <i>alnifolia</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>arbuscula</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>velutinus</i>, <i>Chrysothamnus</i> <i>viscidiflorus</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>nauseosa</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>virginiana</i>, <i>Purshia</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Ribes</i> <i>cereum</i>, <i>Rosa</i> <i>woodsii</i> and <i>Tetradymia</i> <i>canescens</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Juniperus</i> <i>occidentalis</i> Associated herbs include <i>Bromus</i> <i>tectorum</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>idahoensis</i> and <i>Poa</i> <i>secunda</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Emergent trees may be present at low cover. Shrubs < 1 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse or intermittently grassy. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Artemisia tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i> > 10% absolute cover in the shrub canopy (NatureServe 2007).</li>
		
		<li><i>Artemisia tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Artemisia tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i> and/or <i>Symphoricarpos rotundifolius</i> are >50% relative cover in the shrub layer (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Artemisia tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i> , <i>A. tridentata</i> ssp. <i>spiciformis</i> , and/or <i>Symphoricarpos rotundifolius</i>  are > 50% relative cover in the shrub layer (Ratchford et al. 2022b)</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Mountain slopes, drainages, valley bottoms. Soils are loamy, 45-100 cm deep, with gravel and rock fragments.  </div>
</div>

        
